This change allows us to use a custom `name` specified in Vue component and to avoid if there is any duplication in components.

Example:

```vue

// ./components/ui/SidebarTogglerComponent.vue

<template>
    <a class="nav-link" @click="toggle">
        <i class="fa fa-fw fa-bars"></i>
    </a>
</template>

<script>
    export default {
        name: "ui-sidebar-toggler-component",

        methods: {
            toggle() {
                // Toggle the sidebar
            }
        }
    }
</script>
```

Then you can use it like this: `<ui-sidebar-toggler-component></ui-sidebar-toggler-component>`

