The migrations folder was moved from `(:bundle)/migrations` to `(:bundle)/db/migrations`. (This includes `application`.) Additionally, a `(:bundle)/db/seeds` directory was added.

In the `seeds` directory, classes may be created to seed the database, like so:

``` php

<?php

// file: application/db/seeds/roles.php

class Roles
{
    public function run()
    {
        // Insert roles, e.g.
        Role::create(array('name' => 'admin', ...));
    }
}

```

If the seed is part of a bundle - in order to avoid naming conflicts - the class is prefixed by the bundle name, as with tasks. So, the `roles` seed of the `admin` bundle would look like this:

``` php

<?php

// file: bundles/admin/db/seeds/roles.php

class Admin_Roles
{
    public function run()
    {
        ...
    }
}

```

To run all seeds for all bundles, `php artisan migrate:seed`. To run all seeds for the "admin" bundle, `php artisan migrate:seed admin`.

